A.	Within-studies variance (i.e., random error within studies)

B.	Between-studies variance (i.e., variance of the distribution of the true effects across studies)

1 / 1 point

A.


B.


Both A. and B.


Neither A. or B.

Correct
5. Question 5
Which of the following is TRUE about the Tau-squared estimate?

(SELECT ALL THAT APPLY)

1 / 1 point

If the number of studies is large, then the estimate of Tau-squared will have poor precision.


Tau-squared is an estimate of the between-studies variance

Correct

Tau-squared is an estimate of the within-studies variance.


Tau-squared is the total of the estimates of the within-studies and between-studies variances.